Application Security Engineer at Endurance International Group
































Search powered by
Algolia



















Endurance International Group is hiring an
Application Security Engineer







Waltham, United States



General Summary
Develops processes, procedures, and technical implementation of security solutions to enhance the security capabilities of Endurance International Group Inc.’s products and engineering processes. Responsible for providing expertise in the areas of secure coding, secure testing, intellectual property protection, and export control. Assists in the execution complex security architecture reviews according priorities.
Principal Duties and Responsibilities 

Develops, deploys, and maintains security testing programs and tooling
Assists in the creation of security guidance related to product requirements, abuse cases, and attack personas
Assists in the design and operation of the Endurance International Group Inc. external security researcher program
Assists in the compliance with export control initiatives
Engages with engineering leadership in the identification and protection of intellectual property assets
Develops, deploys, and maintains a security advocate/champion program
Develops, deploys, and maintains source code scanning infrastructure
Contributes expertise to help determine requirements and functional specifications for entire organization. 
Works effectively with cross-functional and/or global teams, readily shares information with others. 
Manages, coaches, leads, and develops a small staff of information risk professionals
Participates in Architectural reviews 

Skills

Possesses strong engineering/security/risk/legal knowledge. 
Knowledge of the engineering aspects of information security subject matters including 
Code level knowledge of Java, Javascript, Python , Ruby, Swift and mobile OS
Knowledge of code scanning vendors
In-depth knowledge of various black and white-box security testing techniques
Advanced knowledge of risk assessment design and delivery
Knowledge of automated Web application testing tools 
Problem solving skills. 
Preferred background in quality assurance and/or release engineering
Ability to work in a team environment.
Excellent communication and influencing skills
Project management skills.
Knowledge of the product security aspects of information security subject matter including
Ability to work in a team environment.

Nice to have

Product Security frameworks [BSIMM, OpenSAMM]
SAAS and Mobile software engineering practices
Intellectual Property protection concepts [Code Signing, Code Obfuscation, Open Source]
US Export Control regulations related to cryptography
Knowledge of privacy-by- design concepts

Education Required: Bachelors (Technical) or equivalent, industry certification required [CSSLP and/or Security Testing certifications [GWAPT, CPEN, CEH] preferred]Experience Required: 8+ years relevant experiencePhysical Requirements: No





